The staff here is really excellent. If you live around here & need a spot to make yourself a regular, I highly recommend The Little Whiskey. As another reviewer has said, this is the only place I've been where the staff has gone out of their way to learn my name & who I am, these guys genuinely care about this place. It's not huge but it is clean, they play good music (and important sports games when needed), they have a respectable liquor selection that is extremely reasonably priced. They even make these pretty damn good grilled cheese sandwiches whenever they're open. I don't often see the place packed with people, but many nights that's why I come here. I work late hours & oftentimes just want a place to stop for a Manhattan or two before I finish my walk home & man this place is so perfect for me in that respect. This place is very much worth checking out.

Love this place.... I don't know where to begin, but I'll start by saying it's one of the few bars in the neighborhood where the staff will go out of their way to remember your name and make you feel welcome. The place is clean. SERIOUSLY CLEAN. Drinks are reasonably priced and the music is always great. It definitely has its regulars and that's a good thing. Once you become a regular yourself you'll make friends... it's easy. It's not glamorous or trendy, and that's the best part about it. Nothing pretentious about it. It's a bar for drinkers. If you're a friendly and normal person, you'll find yourself coming back.

I've been here weekend (11am-3pm)  and late weekday nights (9pm-12am).  This will be a review for the times that I have been here.  Weekend afternoons- Very laid back. There was an extremely charismatic bartender that provided tremendous service.  Weekday nights- They have sports, but this is not a sports bar. As a result, music and broadcast audio will alternate between commercial breaks. Depending on the availability of the bartender, you may miss some of the broadcast audio - NOT TERRIBLE, but minor annoyance. The nighttime bartender is wonderful too btw.  So... the staff is top notch, but what keeps this place from being 5 stars is the lack of food options and unusual seating choices around the bar. The tables in the bar would make more sense if it served food, but they're awkwardly placed and make watching big sports events here cumbersome. Really only a problem when it is busy.  It also points because it has a jukebox. A curated playlist develops better bar identity than a jukebox.  4/5  The drinks are well priced - $10-12 cocktails, $4-8 beers.
